ing and crying out miserably.  Snared foes remain prone for the rest of the round and can be struck by the other end of the staff which has a small blade mounted in it.  The staff becomes as flexible as a snake as soon as someone is snared so the blade ca
n 
be used to strike them.  The blade does normal d6 +S damage though it disregards all armor and counts as an enchanted weapon for purposes of attacking.  The blade may only be used to strike those who are already prone due to the net.  With a successful co
ol test at the end of the round the victim will break free and can fight normally in the following round.  Failure means that the victim spends the entire next round prone as before.  If the holder of the snare if hurt the net automatically comes off of t
he victim\rquote s head.  The weapon may only be used against humanoid creatures that are less than ten feet tall.
\par 
